description: Located steps from Thomas Park/Telegraph Hill Monument, this beautifully maintained second-floor condo offers an abundance of natural light and classic charm. Features include cherry hardwood floors throughout, high vaulted ceilings with crown molding and wainscoting, and bay windows in the living room. The open-concept kitchen boasts granite countertops, stainless steel appliances, and a center island that flows into the living area—perfect for entertaining. The spacious bedroom is privately situated in the rear with custom built-ins in the closet. The bathroom offers a granite vanity, tub/shower combo, and generous storage space. Enjoy the convenience of laundry room in-unit with built-in shelving and storage, plus your own private deck, newly redone in 2025 with low-maintenance Trex decking. Freshly painted common areas and a low condo fee make this an exceptional value for first-time buyers or investors. Conveniently located near restaurants, shops, beach & public transportation!
